# User Context

Batav has a basic interface called User Context. This interface is used

- As the link between the authentication mechanism and the case team.
- To support multitenancy. The field context is used to speci

The user context consists of a user name, set of roles and Context. An authenticator must provide this information, typically by fetching it from an IDP.

Any actions on a case instance can only be invokes when a User Context is given.
